<?xml version="1.0"?>
<package >
  <metadata>
    <id>Cinteros.XrmToolBox.BulkDataUpdater</id>
    <version>1.0.0</version>
    <title>Bulk Data Updater for XrmToolBox</title>
    <authors>Jonas Rapp</authors>
    <owners>rappen</owners>
    <projectUrl>https://github.com/rappen/BulkDataUpdater</projectUrl>
    <iconUrl>https://raw.githubusercontent.com/rappen/BulkDataUpdater/master/images/BDU-150-tsp.png</iconUrl>
    <requireLicenseAcceptance>false</requireLicenseAcceptance>
    <description>This tool is useful to trigger workflows or plugins, as well as bulk updating any number of records with fixed values. It can also delete records by the filter specified.</description>
    <summary>Update or touch attributes on a set of records, or delete the data set completely.</summary>
    <releaseNotes>
Latest version:

#29 Added option to wait between calls to server. Thanks Mats Sundbergh @cint-mats!
#28 XML attribute values with only space got trimmed, now fixed.
#26 Incorrect warning text during Delete.
#25 Errors were always ignored during Delete, not anymore.
Fixed tab-order for usability.
Rebranded for 2019.

---

Version 1.2018.10.2:

#1 Option to only update/delete selected records
#3 ExecuteMultiple for updates to improve performance
#16 Retrieve all pages instead of just first page (5000 records)
#21 Bulk Data Updater can now Bulk Delete too
#22 Added possibility to cancel long running operations
#24 Edit XML window did not resize well
    </releaseNotes>
